<font color="#FF0000">30 YEARS AGO, THEN &amp; NOW</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 11 22:07:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
30 years ago, BOOMBOX BOMBERS, flew overhead announcing to the enemy that we would soon be staging an operation in what we called Arizona Territory. <br><br>
On the night of November 11th, we picked up a radio broadcast from Hanoi Hanna warning us to stay out of Arizona territory. She named our company by name;<br>
 <br>
&quot;Suicide India Comapny, Mahreene, if you come into Arizona territory, it will be your suicide. We will be waiting for you, Mahreene. You will die in the open rice paddies and a new GI that stayed home will marry your girlfriend.  It will be Suicide for you if you cross the river, we will be waiting for you, in Arizona Territory, Mahreene.&quot;<br><br>
We would loose over 1/4 of our company in the next few days, only 12 of the 47 in our platoon, 1st platoon would return without getting killed or wounded. <br><br>
I wonder how many who served and died defending our nation would do so today, for the country we have become? 
